Last week, Dr Aceng said the country is expecting to receive donations and directly purchase vaccines from China. 

The Ministry hopes to receive donations of the vaccine from Covax facility by March. 

The Ugandan Parliament has also approved a down payment of Shs18.5 billion for AstraZeneca vaccine from Serum Institute of India. Kenyan buses pick up the children every morning and take them to Kenya. The West bought billions of vaccines fast and cheap, leaving poorer nations paying through the nose for years to come. Referendum is as good as confirmed since the decision of the bicameral Parliament will still result in a blebiscite, anyway. Kositany insists that they will not be pushed into leading the ‘No’ camp.